                                            <footer class="notes"><h2 data-aid="138773482" id="notetitle1">Notas</h2><ol class="decimal" data-type="marker" start="1"><li class="footnote" id="note1-"><span class="label">1. </span><p data-aid="138773484" id="note1_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/pgp/moses/5.html?verse=8#p8" href="/scriptures/pgp/moses/5.8?lang=spa#p8">Moisés 5:8</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note2-"><span class="label">2. </span><p data-aid="138773485" id="note2_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.html?verse=17#p17" href="/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.17?lang=spa#p17">Mosíah 3:17</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note3-"><span class="label">3. </span><p data-aid="138773487" id="note3_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/18.html?verse=23#p23" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/18.23?lang=spa#p23">Doctrina y Convenios 18:23</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note4-"><span class="label">4. </span><p data-aid="138773488" id="note4_p1">Véase de Dallin H. Oaks, “El tomar sobre nosotros el nombre de Cristo”, <em>Liahona,</em> julio de 1985, pág. 79.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note5-"><span class="label">5. </span><p data-aid="138773490" id="note5_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/18.html?verse=24#p24" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/18.24?lang=spa#p24">Doctrina y Convenios 18:24</a>; cursiva agregada.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note6-"><span class="label">6. </span><p data-aid="138773492" id="note6_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/dc-testament/dc/20.html?verse=37#p37" href="/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/20.37?lang=spa#p37">Doctrina y Convenios 20:37</a>; cursiva agregada.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note7-"><span class="label">7. </span><p data-aid="138773493" id="note7_p1">El presidente Dallin H. Oaks enseñó: “… tomamos sobre